            <p class="text-gray">Heads or Tails is a game variant patterned after coin flipping or coin tossing. It is played by rolling down three coins after inserting/loading them on the top slot of a transparent acrylic slide at the same time. Once the three coins finally settle on the floor, the majority side wins the game.</p><br>
            <p class="text-gray">Coins are colored red on one side with bold letter H and blue on the other side with bold letter T for easier identification.</p><br> <br>
